      "starts_with_paragraph_marker": true,
      "paragraph_box_xyxy": [
        55,
        173,
        572,
        365
      ],
      "text": "\nThe Duvalier regime has long been almost totally dependent on the President's repressive security police for survival. The armed forces, weakened and alienated by a series of purges designed to eliminate officers of questionable loyalty to Duvalier, could not be relied on to support the government. A prolonged economic and financial crisis and inefficient administration have further weakened the government, and it seems doubtful that the regime could hold together if Duvalier's illness should spark serious disorders.",
